  "cataloging_subject": {
    "id": "work:CME00078",
    "unit_type": "edited_selection",
    "label": "An English Friend of Charles of Orléans: Sections B–E",
    "scope_note": "The 33 Middle English lyrics selected as sections B–E of Henry Noble MacCracken's 1911 article and encoded as CME00078. This is an editorially assembled selection, not one securely attributable medieval work or one manuscript anthology: section B is the Fairfax Sequence; section C gathers nine English poems from manuscripts associated with Charles d'Orléans; section D prints two lyrics from Royal MS 16 F II; and section E juxtaposes poems from Arundel MS 26 and the Findern manuscript. Modern editorial framing, French comparison texts, and the physical manuscripts are modeled in lineage rather than merged into the intellectual work."
  },
